<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="132" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
Species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scarabaeoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scarabaeoidea (Schonnherria)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">Schonnherria</taxonomicName>
are small (15 mm) to moderately large bees (~24 mm), often with metallic highlights on all tagmata. 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scarabaeoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scarabaeoidea (Schonnherria)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">Schonnherria</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other New World subgenera of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xylocopa</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: female mandible bidentate (except tridentate in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa viridigastra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridigastra">Xylocopa viridigastra</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau, 1841), with apical tooth about as broad as or broader than basal tooth; T1 with complete gradulus on both sexes, remaining terga with gradulus absent (except in the male of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa bambusae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bambusae">Xylocopa bambusae</taxonomicName>
with gradulus also on T2); male genitalia with a large spine of the ventral margin of the gonocoxite and the apex of the gonostylus bifid.
</paragraph>
